name: overachieve
content:
Add to word list
Add to word list
to do more than is expected or be more successful than others: Some of our programs will overachieve; some may fall short. He is a graduate of a prestigious university, who likes to overachieve. Compare
underachieve
overachievement noun [ U ]
Her early life was marked by intense overachievement. overachieving adjective [ before noun ]
He is an overachieving dot-com millionaire, and prize-winning filmmaker.
